<paragraph id="BB277CCABA060ECA178AB17D765131F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
<bibRefCitation id="1EF10B5B4A7C7FAA4358FD2DC0431377" author="Licher, F" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 336" title="Revision der Gattung Typosyllis Langerhans, 1879 (Polychaeta: Syllidae). Morphologie, Taxonomie und Phylogenie." volume="551" year="1999">Licher (1999)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="B7096DFBA4C85ACCB0E041BB9060E09D" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllis truncata" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="subSpecies" species="truncata" subSpecies="cryptica">Syllis truncata cryptica</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4B06C696ECBE8AA038D67C820ACF6D68" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllis gerlachi" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="gerlachi">Syllis gerlachi</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="4A75697C26285C8466D3E71423FA1FC5" author="San Martin, Guillermo" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="201 - 243" title="The genus Syllis Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Annelida: Syllidae: Syllinae) from Australia (second part): four new species and re-description of twelve previously described species" volume="4237" year="2017">
San 
<normalizedToken id="111C191EA32844F26275060CBDF94F8E" originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
et al. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
examined the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="D7E101996C1AF7CA43164D67D83A9563" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllis gerlachi" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="gerlachi">Syllis gerlachi</taxonomicName>
and found it to differ from Mediterranean specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="8C4FA44D3B9347BB8BF87BC24CA601DD" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllis truncata" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="subSpecies" species="truncata" subSpecies="cryptica">Syllis truncata cryptica</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the posterior aciculae and other chaetal features (no exact details given). They consider the synonymy incorrect, but as they do not formally re-instate 
<taxonomicName id="BF8F26558F467A10AAB1FBC4999078FA" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllis truncata" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="subSpecies" species="truncata" subSpecies="cryptica">Syllis truncata cryptica</taxonomicName>
, we here report records of both species under the name 
<taxonomicName id="A3F3041C8FCD37BB280C58D86C12606F" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Syllis gerlachi" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="gerlachi">Syllis gerlachi</taxonomicName>
until further evidence is provided.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
